In article <CE3wL8.13C@dcs.ed.ac.uk> pdc@dcs.ed.ac.uk (Paul Crowley) writes:
>Perhaps a "these people are
>different" signature is needed, which verifies that two public key
>holders have been seen in the same room at the same time.  

Of course, if there are N public key holders, you wind up with a total
of N^2 signatures, N for each holder.  This could make for some really
big key rings.
